==Draynor Village: A paint job==
{{Map|3105,3259|name=Gregg|npcid=10638|mtype=pin|ptype=npc|align=right|group=Gregg}}
===Introduction with Gregg===
* '''Gregg:''' *sigh* Hi there... Happy Easter... I guess...
* '''Player:''' Happy? You don't sound too happy about it?
* '''Gregg:''' I'm just tired of Easter, really.
* '''Gregg:''' Easter just seems to be about rabbits, so whenever a rabbit shows up all anyone can think of is 'Ooh look at the Easter Rabbit!'.
* '''Gregg:''' I want to go out and explore Gielinor, but nobody takes me seriously enough to let me travel.
* '''Gregg:''' Meanwhile, all the other holidays have a bunch of cool stuff associated with them so nobody bats an eyelid when a zombie shambles through town.
* '''Gregg:''' The goblins even got to keep their stupid sled track from Christmas!
* {{tcond|If the player has a [[RuneScape:Varbit/11732|personal best time on the sled track]]:}}
** '''Player:''' That sledding course is pretty fun, actually.
** '''Gregg:''' *sigh* I'm sure it is, human. I tried to go on it myself but the goblins kept mobbing me about Easter eggs.
** '''Gregg:''' I told them they'd have to wait until Easter like everybody else, but they wouldn't have any of it!
* '''Gregg:''' I dunno. I just feel like as long as I live, I'm gonna be an advertisement for Easter and nothing more.
* '''Player:''' Poor guy. Can't be nice having life's doors slammed in your face all the time.
* '''Gregg:''' *sigh* Yeah...
* '''Gregg:''' ... Wait a second...
* '''Gregg:''' Doors... Easter.... Doors... East... Doors... Eastdo-
* '''Gregg:''' Human! I've got it! Eastdoor!
* '''Player:''' ... What?
* {{tact|continue}}

===What if these people were given something else to celebrate with...===
* '''Gregg:''' Humans only care about rabbits for Easter decorations, right? Well, what if we give these people something else to celebrate with?
* '''Gregg:''' Then you can have your Easter and I can be a rabbit!
* '''Player:''' And you plan to do this with... doors?
* '''Gregg:''' Eastdoors!
* '''Player:''' Joke names aside, are you sure this will work?
* '''Gregg:''' Well... no, not really.
* '''Gregg:''' But hey, anything that takes the spotlight off us rabbits can't hurt! Plus, it could be fun!
* {{tact|continue}}

===An offer to help===
* '''Gregg:''' What do you say, human? Do you want to help?
* {{topt|Yes}}<!--No punctuation-->
** {{tact|continue}}<!--Varbit 11951 changed: 2 -> 4-->
* {{topt|No}}<!--No punctuation-->
** '''Gregg:''' ... Oh. Well, I'll be here if you change your mind, I guess.<!--Varbit 11951 changed: 2 -> 3-->
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Gregg after a refusal====
* '''Gregg:''' Have you changed your mind, human?
* {{topt|Yes}}<!--No punctuation-->
** {{tact|continue}}<!--Varbit 11951 changed: 3 -> 4-->
* {{topt|No}}<!--No punctuation-->
** {{tact|above}}

===Once the player has accepted to help===
* '''Gregg:''' Eggcellent! This is going to be the best Easter ever! Now, where to start...
* '''Gregg:''' Hmm... all these brown doors aren't particularly Eastery... We should probably start by painting them.
* '''Gregg:''' I think I have all of my supplies on me... brushes... pallette... safety goggles...<!--Where did he get the idea to bring these before thinking of Eastdoors? 🐇-->
* '''Gregg:''' Oh, ghosh darn, I'm fresh out of paint!
* '''Player:''' I think there's a witch nearby who makes dyes. Maybe she has some paint?
* {{tact|continue}}

===Acquiring pastel flowers and Gregg's iou from Gregg===
* {{tact|above}}
* '''Gregg:''' Couldn't hurt to ask, I guess. If I give you some flowers to use as ingredients, can you ask her for some paint?<!--Varbit 11951 changed: 4 -> 5-->
* '''Player:''' I'll speak to Aggie, give me the ingredients.
* {{topt|cond=If the player has never received the ingredients before, and/or interrupted the above dialogue:|I'll speak to Aggie, give me the ingredients.}}<!--Varbit 11951 == 5-->
** {{tcond|If the player is missing both [[Gregg's iou]] and [[pastel flowers]], and the player does not have at least two free inventory spaces:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' Hmm... Human, I don't think you have enough room in your pockets for more things.
*** '''Gregg:''' There's a Bank just south down the road. You can go there to drop off a few items if you want to make space.
*** {{tcond|If the player is an [[Ultimate Ironman|Ultimate Iron(wo)man]]:}}
**** '''Player:''' Bank? I've never been so insulted in my entire life!
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player is missing the pastel flowers and Gregg's iou, and the player has at least two free inventory spaces:}}
*** {{tbox|Gregg hands you a bunch of pastel-coloured flowers and an IOU for 5 coins.}}
*** {{tact|receives=pastel flowers, Gregg's iou}}
*** '''Player:''' This is... a piece of paper?
*** '''Gregg:''' It's an IOU. We rabbits don't usually carry cash on us, I'm afraid.
*** {{tact|previous}}
* {{topt|Why don't you go?}}
** '''Player:''' If you have the ingredients on you, why not go ask her yourself?
** '''Gregg:''' I... Human, I honestly don't think I could stomach going.
** '''Player:''' Witches aren't that scary. I'm sure Aggie is lovely once you get to know her.
** '''Gregg:''' It's not that, it's... I just don't want to be ridiculed for being an Easter bunny.
** '''Gregg:''' I've put up with being the 'cute widdle wabbit' my whole life. I don't think I can take much more of it.
** '''Player:''' Poor guy.
** {{tact|previous}}
* {{topt|What am I meant to be doing again?}}
** '''Player:''' So, uh... what am I meant to be doing again?
** '''Gregg:''' You've forgotten already? Silly human!
** {{tcond|If the player has never received the ingredients:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' You were about to take some ingredients off me to give to the nice dye-making witch in exchange for some paint!
** {{tcond|If the player has received the ingredients at least once before, irregardless if they are currently in the player's inventory or not:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' You were about to take the ingredients from me to that nice dye-making witch in the house down that alley behind the wheelbarrow!
** '''Gregg:''' We were going to use it to decorate some doors in the spirit of Easter so people associate it less with rabbits!
** '''Player:''' This seems... awfully convoluted.
** '''Gregg:''' Yep!
** {{tact|previous}}
* {{topt|Goodbye.}}
** '''Player:''' Goodbye.
** '''Gregg:''' So long, human! I'll be here if you need anything.
** {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Gregg after receiving the ingredients once, before receiving a thick dye====
* {{topt|cond=If the player has received the ingredients at least once before, and never received a [[thick dye]] from [[Aggie]]:|Do you have more ingredients?}}<!--Varbit 11951 == 6-->
** {{tcond|If the player is missing both Gregg's iou and pastel flowers, and the player does not have at least two free inventory spaces:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' I do, but you'd need to make more space in your pockets first.
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player has Gregg's iou but not the pastel flowers, and the player does not have at least one free inventory space:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' I can give you more flowers, but you'd need to make more space in your pockets first.
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player has the pastel flowers but not Gregg's iou, and the player does not have at least one free inventory space:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' I can give you another IOU, but you'd need to make more space in your pockets first.
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player has the pastel flowers but not Gregg's iou, and the player has at least one free inventory space:}}
*** Gregg quickly scratches up a new IOU for 5 coins.
*** {{tact|receives=Gregg's iou}}
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player has Gregg's iou but not the pastel flowers, and the player has at least one free inventory space:}}
*** Gregg hands you another bunch of pastel-coloured flowers.
*** {{tact|receives=pastel flowers}}
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player is missing the pastel flowers and Gregg's iou, and the player has at least two free inventory spaces:}}
*** Gregg hands you another bunch of pastel-coloured flowers and an IOU for 5 coins.
*** {{tact|receives=pastel flowers, Gregg's iou}}
*** '''Gregg:''' Try not to lose these ones. If people find my IOUs, I'm gonna have quite the bill to pay!
*** {{tact|previous}}
** {{tcond|If the player has both Gregg's iou and pastel flowers:}}
*** '''Gregg:''' Silly human! You have the ingredients on you already!
*** '''Gregg:''' You need to take them to the witch who makes dyes you mentioned. Aggie, I think her name.
*** '''Player:''' I just thought you might like more than one load of paint.
*** '''Gregg:''' Hmmm... maybe, but let's get one first and see how we get on.
*** {{tact|previous}}
* Why don't you go?
** {{tact|above}}
* What am I meant to be doing again?
** {{tact|above}}
* Goodbye.
** {{tact|above}}

====Reading Gregg's iou====
<blockquote>I promise to pay the bearer on demand the sum of five (5) gold coins.

Signed,<br>
Gregg The Rabbit

P.S. Happy Easter :D</blockquote>

====Using Gregg's iou on Gregg====
* '''Gregg:''' Silly human, you're meant to give that to the nice witch down the road, not me!
* '''Player:''' Could I have some coins instead?
* '''Gregg:''' Human, if I had coins to give you, I wouldn't have given you an IOU in the first place!
* {{tact|end}}

====Using pastel flowers on Gregg====
* '''Gregg:''' Silly human, you're meant to give that to the nice witch down the road, not me!
* '''Player:''' Which witch, sorry?
* '''Gregg:''' I think she's just down that street there, in the house with the wheelbarrow in front of it.
* {{tact|end}}

===Asking Aggie to make a thick dye===
* {{topt|cond=If the player has received the ingredients from Gregg at least once before, all the time while the Easter event is active:|Ask about the Easter event.}}
** '''Player:''' Hello, I have a pigment problem I was told you might be able to help with.
** '''Aggie:''' What can I help you with?
** '''Player:''' Can you make paint?
** '''Aggie:''' Paint? Hmmm... If you have some ingredients I might be able to come up with something. I'll also want payment, mind.
** {{tcond|If the player is missing pastel flowers in the inventory:}}
*** '''Player:''' Ingredients? Hmmm... I should probably go and get those then.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has pastel flowers in the inventory, but not Gregg's iou or 5 coins:}}
*** '''Player:''' I don't have anything to pay you with...
*** '''Aggie:''' Then I suggest you leave until you do.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has pastel flowers and 5 coins in the inventory, but not Gregg's iou:}}
*** '''Player:''' Is this any good?
*** You show Aggie the pastel-colorued{{sic|pastel-coloured}} flowers.
*** '''Aggie:''' Hm... There's definitely some good colours there, but I don't have anything that'd make it thick enough as well.
*** {{tbox|Perhaps you should bring Gregg's IOU as well.}}
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has pastel flowers and Gregg's iou in the inventory:}}
*** '''Player:''' Is this any good?
*** {{tbox|You show Aggie the pastel-coloured flowers and Gregg's IOU.}}
*** '''Aggie:''' This... is an IOU?
*** '''Player:''' Uh, yeah, my friend gave it to me...
*** '''Aggie:''' Hmm... your friend wouldn't happen to be that Easter bunny out in front of Ned's house, would it?
*** '''Player:''' I... uhh...
*** '''Aggie:''' Because he is so unbelievably adorable! And this note is so cute! I love it!
*** '''Aggie:''' I tell you what; I don't have any 'paint', per se, but I think I might have something.
*** '''Aggie:''' A while back someone gave me an order to make a bunch of cyan dye, but they never came to collect it.
*** '''Aggie:''' It's been sat in the cupboard for a while and has dried up and thickened a fair amount.
*** '''Aggie:''' I bet it's gotten thick enough to use as paint, meanwhile I can use those flowers to get a fresh batch going!
*** '''Player:''' That sounds great!
*** {{tbox|You swap the flowers and Gregg's IOU for a bottle of thickened dye.}}<!--Varbit 11951 changed: 6 -> 7-->
*** {{tact|Player loses pastel flowers and Gregg's IOU.}}
*** {{tact|receives=a [[Thick dye]]}}
*** {{tact|continue}}
* {{topt|event=No|Ask about something else.}}

====After-chat with Aggie after swapping the items====
* '''Aggie:''' You know, it's funny...
* '''Aggie:''' The people of Draynor aren't usually a festive bunch, but this year everyone seems down right miserable.<!--Years 2020-2021 were known for a global pandemic at the time.-->
* '''Aggie:''' And this is coming from a witch who just sits around a cauldron all day!<!--A depressed developer projecting their life into a script?-->
* '''Aggie:''' But hopefully you and your cute bunny friend are able to bring some seasonal cheer to us, Guthix knows we need it...
* {{tact|end}}

====Talking to Aggie after making the thick dye once====
* {{tcond|If the player has a thick dye in inventory before giving one to Gregg, or has already given a thick dye to Gregg:}}
** '''Player:''' I just wanted to say thanks again for the dye.
** '''Aggie:''' Don't mention it, as long as your cute little bunny friend is happy I'm happy.
** '''Aggie:''' You should probably go see if he needs anything else, I think he's still outside Ned's house.
** {{tact|end}}
* {{tcond|If the player does not have a thick dye and hasn't given one to Gregg yet:}}
** '''Player:''' You wouldn't happen to have any more dye, would you?
** {{tcond|If the player's inventory is full:}}
*** '''Aggie:''' Certainly, but you don't seem to have the room to take some right now. Go make some space in your inventory and come back to me.
*** {{tact|end}}
** {{tcond|If the player has at least one free inventory space:}}
*** '''Aggie:''' Certainly, here you go.
*** Aggie hands you another bottle of thickened dye.
*** {{tact|receives=a thick dye}}
*** '''Aggie:''' Be careful not to lose it this time.
*** {{tact|end}}

